title: Tiffany Hartwell Memorial Window Boxed Note Cards
description:
Cards developed from (attributed to) Agnes F. Northrop and Tiffany Studios’, Hartwell Memorial Window, 1917, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

The Hartwell Memorial Window, 1917 is one of the most extraordinary leaded glass windows ever made by Tiffany Studios, the leading glass firm of America’s Gilded Age. The cards are made from a sustainable FSC certified mix paper and vegetable-based inks.

  • Card dimensions: 5 x 7 in.
  • Box dimensions: 5.625 x 7.625 x 1.375 in.
  • 20 cards and envelopes; 4 cards each of 5 images.
